title: Medial icosacronic hexecontahedron
summary: In geometry, the medial icosacronic hexecontahedron (or midly sagittal ditriacontahedron) is a nonconvex isohedral polyhedron. It is the dual of the uniform icosidodecadodecahedron. Its faces are darts. Part of each dart lies inside the solid, hence is invisible in solid models.
